&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Médicos Sin Fronteras en México A.C.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seeks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entomologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;for International Humanitarian Missions&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;To join our team in International Projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Field-based – DURATION 9-12 months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Starting date September 2026; HR benefits and type of contract based on country of residence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*** Please upload your CV (2 pages maximum) and motivation letter in English ***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS JOB PROFILE IS IN ENGLISH SINCE THIS IS THE REQUIRED LANGUAGE FOR THE JOB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;MSF has been present in the Central American region for nearly 50 years, with regular projects and emergencies. In Mexico since 2007, the Branch Office has overseen legal representation, fundraising, communications, and HR recruitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;MSF has been in Honduras in different projects, including natural disasters, people on the move, epidemics, healthcare exclusion. Our current project in Tegucigalpa´s goal is to reduce the morbidity and mortality related to dengue fever in Tegucigalpa, with a focus on prevention, early detection, epidemiological and entomological monitoring, and proper clinical treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;In order to better serve patients and population needs in Central America and Mexico, we want to harness the full potential of the people, capacities, and resources in the region and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;We commit to developing an interconnected, locally led, and inclusive approach to operational management, operational support, and associative engagement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;We will increase capacity for decision-making for operations and implementation of the social mission in the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OBJECTIVE OF THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Organizing, implementing and designing the aspects related to understanding the malaria vector in the project according to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;MSF&lt;/strong&gt;’s protocols, tools and procedures in order to ensure quality medical care in the community and improve the population’s health condition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the assessment and prioritization of vector control interventions by working jointly with the Project and Management teams to evaluate implementation needs when identified at project level, providing technical input to inform operational planning and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in capacity building, design, improvement and implementation of vector control as support for MoH programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical accompaniment to the strengthening of entomological surveillance in Honduras, supporting technical discussions, reviews, and coordination with relevant stakeholders, including UNAH, to contribute to improvements of the National Entomological Surveillance Protocol.&

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Médicos Sin Fronteras en México A.C.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seeks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;ER &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Doctor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;for International Humanitarian Missions&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;To join our team in International Projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;(Minimum availability of 6 months)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*** Please upload your CV and motivation letter in English ***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS JOB PROFILE IS IN ENGLISH SINCE THIS IS THE REQUIRED LANGUAGE FOR THE JOB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OBJECTIVE OF THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The emergency doctor supervises the operation of the Emergency Service, from the admission to the discharge of the patients, according to the objectives of the project and in relation to the other services of the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an ER physician, you are responsible for providing the best medical care to the patient and are involved in the triage system, patient flow, and protocol implementation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It guarantees the training and supervision of national personnel. For the purposes of knowledge transfer, the training consists of both theoretical and head training to ensure a gradual transfer of responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply medical knowledge and skills for diagnosis and prevention. Carry out outpatient and hospital consultations, prescribing the necessary treatment respecting MSF protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the patient and their family informed about the disease and give appropriate explanations about the treatment to be followed, verifying that they have understood it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the evolution of hospitalized patients / IDP through daily visits, consultations and exams. Prescribe the necessary treatment following MSF protocols, deciding in collaboration with other doctors whether patients should be discharged or transferred to other departments, and informing their families about the patient&#39;s progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify and control under his responsibility the rational distribution of medicines and equipment, and take care of the quality, disinfection and sterilization of medical equipment. Ensure compliance with hygiene standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the collection and analysis of epistemological data, verifying the validity and informing the person in charge or coordinator of the field about any problem or complication in the patient&#39;s illness, or medical error. Controls the proper functioning of the department, equipment or material.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure continuous training of the multidisciplinary medical / paramedical team to optimize the quality of care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knows and ensures that all MSF medical protocols are still being implemented, verifying that universal precautions are followed at all times, reducing risks of biohazard and improving infection control. Ensures that professional confidentiality is respected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages the team under his responsibility in accordance with MSF&#39;s HR policies and procedures, supervising its performance, organizing and planning shifts and rotations, and directly participating in em

